<html>
<body>
Reports Persistence ORM XML descriptors that cannot be resolved within the configured datasource
and suggests refreshing the datasource or assigning a different one.

<p><b>Example database table:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="sql">
  CREATE TABLE DATA_TABLE (
    ID INTEGER,
    DATA VARCHAR(100)
  );
</code></pre><br/>

<p><b>Example JSP file:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="jsp">
  &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt;
  &lt;entity-mappings xmlns="http://java.sun.com/xml/ns/persistence/orm" version="1.0"&gt;
    &lt;entity name="JavaEntity" class="JavaEntity"&gt;
        &lt;table name="UNKNOWN_TABLE"/&gt; // Error: unresolved table
        &lt;attributes&gt;
          &lt;id name="id"&gt;
            &lt;column name="ID" nullable="false"/&gt;
          &lt;/id&gt;
          &lt;basic name="UNKNOWN_COLUMN"&gt; // Error: unresolved column
            &lt;column name="UNKNOWN_COLUMN" length="12"/&gt;
          &lt;/basic&gt;
        &lt;/attributes&gt;
    &lt;/entity&gt;
  &lt;/entity-mappings&gt;
</code></pre><br/>
<!-- tooltip end -->
<p>
  <b>NOTE:</b> Datasource can be configured via `Assign datasource` action
</p>
</body>
</html>
